heories of writing; a cultural and social history of the practices that make mutually defining modes of loss and reparation profitable and pleasurable; and a reading of certain literary texts that might lead us to new understandings of the relationship between artistic and commercial discourses in America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362505140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503625051423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503625051/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles